clue: It's a demonstrably true mathematical statement; calculus has a "fundamental" one

response: theorem

clue: Fire up the engine of your mind & name this solid figure with equal & parallel circles at either end

response: a cylinder

clue: Multiply the numerator of one fraction by the denominator of another (& vice versa) to get their "cross" this

response: product

clue: See if you can pick off this term for the point at which a line or curve crosses an axis

response: the intercept

clue: In 19 - 5 = 14 19 is the minuend; 5 is this other "end"

response: the subtrahend

